abstract: Houthi militiamen who forced Yemeni Pres Abdu Rabbu Mansour Hadi to resign continue to occupy key points in capital of Sana, but do not make official claim to power; streets in capital are calm in wake of resignation of Hadi and his cabinet, and Houthi militia says it is waiting for Parliament to approve Hadi's resignation.
lead_paragraph: Houthi militiamen appeared to be consolidating their control, and there were reports that Parliament might reject the president’s resignation.

byline.contributor: Mona El-Naggar reported from Sana, and Rod Nordland from Amman, Jordan. Shuaib Almosawa contributed reporting from Sana.
byline.original: By MONA EL-NAGGAR and ROD NORDLAND

snippet: Houthi militiamen appeared to be consolidating their control, and there were reports that Parliament might reject the president’s resignation.
